&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Overview:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is responsible for safely and efficiently operating radiologic imaging equipment and performing diagnostic imaging on patients in an outpatient procedural facility as ordered by the physician. You may also provide additional support preparing/scrubbing for procedures such as angiograms, venograms, and fistula grams. All activities should be performed consistent with the Radiologic Technician’s education and training, and in accordance with facility policies and procedures and applicable professional standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performs C-Arm Tech Duties: Prepare exam room and equipment to conduct radiologic examinations in accordance with infectious disease, sterilization, and patient safety protocols, policies, and procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists with preparing the patient for the surgical procedure by positioning and prepping&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively operate C-Arm to perform x-rays, practice radiation safety control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify anatomical orientation on all required images and assures proper file identification on all images&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review examination images, finalizing images in PACS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform quality control procedures to ensure that the equipment operates at optimal levels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in prioritizing assigned work based on workflow fluctuations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide detailed and accurate procedure information for collection in databases as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform procedures in compliance with Standards of Care, facility and regulatory requirements, and ARRT Standards of Ethics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain quality standards as it relates to HIPAA regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completing other task as per management request&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Requirements&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of High School diploma or equivalent required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Associate’s degree or Bachelor’s degree in radiography, radiation therapy, or nuclear medicine preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ARRT (American Registry of Radiologic Technologist) state of CT license&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-4 years of experience in as general radiologic technologist preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to communicate with patients, visitors, and employees within the organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willing to be available for local and/or regional assignments as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to adequately use the department&#39;s computerized system and its associated devices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Compensation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;$40/hour - $58/hour. Negotiable based on skills and experience.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
